Air Berlin CEO Aims for 2012 Profit ‘at the Latest,’ WiWo Says

-- B y   C o r n e l i u s   R a h n
-- 
2011-03-04T10:53:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-04/air-berlin-ceo-aims-for-2012-profit-at-the-latest-wiwo-says.html
  Air Berlin Plc (AB1)  aims to return to
profit in 2012 “at the latest” as its entry into the Oneworld
airline alliance helps business,  WirtschaftsWoche  magazine
reported, citing Chief Executive Officer Joachim Hunold.  The company is in talks with candidates who could fill a
new post on its management board and may consider hiring people
from outside  Germany  for the position, the magazine cited Hunold
as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cornelius Rahn in Frankfurt at 
 crahn2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:  Kenneth Wong  in Berlin at 
 kwong11@bloomberg.net  